modules.description: Provides operations for adding, subtracting, and scaling 3D vectors, along with a dot product calculation. Works with records containing x, y, and z fields of type float. Used to compute movement directions and lighting calculations in a graphics application.

Provides vector operations including dot product, cross product, addition, subtraction, scaling, normalization, and magnitude calculations. Works with a three-dimensional float-based vector type, supporting conversions to and from tuples and strings. Used for 3D geometry computations, physics simulations, and spatial transformations.
